PN,39905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1781175772
OL,3,CHundreds of young people to play in
OL,4,CGaelic Football tournament in
OL,5,CManchester
OL,7,FOthers shared family ties to counties
OL,8,Flike Mayo, Galway, and Cork, while
OL,9,Fsome described Gaelic football as a
OL,10,Funique way to connect with their
OL,11,Fheritage and stand out amongst their
OL,12,Fpeers in Manchester.
OL,14,FShane Goldrick, who introduced Gaelic
OL,15,Ffootball to Blessed Thomas Holford's
OL,16,Fcurriculum, explained, "I was lucky
OL,17,Fenough to represent Lancashire and be
OL,18,Fcaptain. Years ago, I brought it into
OL,19,Fthe curriculum, and now all year
OL,20,Fseven, eight, and nine pupils
OL,21,Fexperience Gaelic football."
OL,26,@xD@XOU}D@\O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
